# Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge

We as contributors and maintainers of **ZkLite** pledge to make participation in this project a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body size, disability, ethnicity, gender identity and expression, level of experience, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual orientation.

Our goal is to foster an open, welcoming, respectful, and inclusive community.

---

## Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment include:

- Using welcoming and inclusive language
- Being respectful of differing viewpoints and experiences
- Giving and receiving constructive feedback gracefully
- Focusing on what is best for the community and project
- Showing empathy toward other community members

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

- Harassment, discrimination, or hateful language
- Personal attacks, insults, or derogatory comments
- Trolling, intimidation, or deliberate disruption
- Publishing othersâ€™ private information without consent
- Any conduct that would be considered inappropriate in a professional setting

---

## Scope

This Code of Conduct applies to all project spaces, including but not limited to:

- GitHub repositories
- Issues and pull requests
- Discussions and comments
- Community channels related to ZkLite

It also applies when an individual is representing the project in public spaces.

---

## Enforcement

Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying and enforcing this Code of Conduct.

Unacceptable behavior may result in actions such as:

- Warning the offender
- Temporary or permanent ban from the project
- Removal of content or contributions

All enforcement decisions will be made in good faith and with the goal of maintaining a healthy community.

---

## Reporting

If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior, please report it by contacting the project maintainers.

Reports will be reviewed and handled confidentially where possible.

---

## Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the **Contributor Covenant**, version 2.1  
https://www.contributor-covenant.org/

